{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀντιποι-έω</b>, <br /> <b>do in return,</b> ταῦτα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 50e; ἀντ᾽ εὖ ποιεῖν [prev. author] “Grg.” 520e; οἱ μὴ ἀντιποιοῦντες εὖ 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1397b7; κακῶς μὲν πάσχοντας, ἀντιποιεῖν δὲ οὐ δυναμένους 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.3.12, compare [prev. work] 7; ἀ. κακῶς τὸν ἄρξαντα 1st c.AD: Musonius Philosophus “fragment” 10p.56H.; ἀ. τὸ αὐτό 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1138a22\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to have done to one in turn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.24.19. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i> (<i>aorist</i> <i>passive</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMort.” 29.2)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>], with <i>genitive</i>, <b>exert oneself about</b> a thing, <b>seek after</b> it, ἀ. τῶν σπουδαίων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.2\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>lay claim to,</b> τῆς πόλεως[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.122; ἀρετῆς 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 6.7\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῆς τέχνης, τῶν νικητηρίων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 90d, “Phlb.” 23a; τοῦ πρωτεύειν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 10.52; τῆς θαλάττης 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 190.11; τῶν ἐν τῇ Ἑλλάδι πραγμάτων 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 11.62; οἱ Δωριεῖς ἀντιποιοῦνται τῆς τραγῳδίας 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1448a30: also with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, ἀ. ἐπίστασθαί τι <b>lay claim to</b> knowing.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 91c, compare “Hp.Mi.” 363a: with _accusative_, τὴν κληρονομίαν “Michel” 546.16 (Cappad., 1st c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>contend